This breaks out an `get_expire_seconds` method that simply gets the `EXPIRE_AFTER` value from the config. My thinking is that this should allow things like https://github.com/yourlabs/django-session-security/issues/58 to be solved by the end-user easily though creating a new middleware that overrides the `get_expire_seconds` method. For example, if they want per-user settings they'd have to create a User Profile model to store the timeout, then they could just do something like:

```python
class MySessionSecurityMiddleware(SessionSecurityMiddleware):
    def get_expire_seconds(self, request):
        try:
            return request.user.profile.session_timeout
        except Exception:
            return settings.EXPIRE_AFTER
```

(* example not guaranteed to work)

